yingyinNormal.en: No, actually, I think that they're, gas. Gas? Wow. Intense.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不是，其实是瓦斯炉。瓦斯炉？真带劲。

yingyinNormal.en: So this is being a parent? I think I can handle this. Too intense. Too intense.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以这就是带孩子，是吧？我想我可以处理得很好的。太难了，太难了。

yingyinNormal.en: OK. Quite intense. This, I feel, just really earthy and just really compliments the soy and then, simply, just before serving, a couple of drizzles.

yingyinNormal.en: For visitors, Hong Kong offers some of the world's most intense shopping, sightseeing and dining experiences, yet moments of stillness await at every turn.

yingyinNormal.en: This change creates the intense experience of happiness, feeling social, increased empathy and the inability to sleep, which is likely why it is such a popular party drug.

intense和intensive均可表示“强烈的”。intense用来形容某种性质或感情，表示很高或达到极端的程度； intensive含有intense的意思，但更强调“精细的；集中的”。例：
intense heat
酷热

两周的强化训练
